e, 'body': "## Bug report \r\nworkflow {\r\n     HELLO()\r\n     HELLO()\r\n}\r\n### Expected behavior and actual behavior\r\nexpected behavior: Run process HELLO twice\r\nactual result : Process 'HELLO' has been already used -- If you need to reuse the same component include it with a different name or include in a different workflow context\r\n\r\n* Nextflow version: 20.10.0 \r\n* Java version: 8\r\n* Operating system: [Ubuntu 18.04]\r\n* Bash version: 5.0.17(1)-release (x86_64-pc-linux-gnu)\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nDSL 2 is enabled.\r\n\r\nis I have any way to run the processes on loop?\r\nsomething like:\r\n    workflow {\r\n     for (int i=0; I< 5; i++){\r\n           HELLO()\r\n     }\r\n}", 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1949/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1949/timeline'}, {'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow', 'category': {'id': 32532274, 'node_id': 'MDE4OkRpc2N1c3Npb25DYXRlZ29yeTMyNTMyMjc0', 'repository_id': 9052236, 'emoji': ':pray:', 'name': 'Q&A', 'description': 'Ask the community for help', 'created_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'updated_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'slug': 'q-a', 'is_answerable': True}, 'answer_html_url': 'https://github.com/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1950#discussioncomment-435901', 'answer_chosen_at': '2021-03-09T23:21:13.000Z', 'answer_chosen_by': {'login': 'timothy-barry', 'id': 33360565, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjMzMzYwNTY1', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33360565?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/timothy-barry', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/timothy-barry', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/timothy-barry/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/timothy-barry/following{/ot