_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': 'Hello,\r\n\r\nI am reading through the Nextflow documentation. I am confused by [something](https://www.nextflow.io/docs/latest/process.html#input-of-files) I read in Processes/Inputs/Input of files. In the example, `proteins` is defined in terms of a file path:\r\n`proteins = Channel.fromPath( \'/some/path/*.fa\' )`.\r\nBut the tip at the bottom says, "This is also the reason why you should avoid whenever possible to use absolute or relative paths referencing files in your pipeline processes." So I have two questions.\r\n\r\n1. When should I be using file paths? At the beginning of the script and never again?\r\n2. What is the base directory of the file path  \'/some/path/*.fa\'? Is it stored in the `baseDir` global variable, as described [here](https://www.nextflow.io/docs/latest/script.html#script-implicit-variables)?\r\n\r\nI am quite new to this, so thanks for the help.', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1950/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1950/timeline'}, {'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow', 'category': {'id': 32532274, 'node_id': 'MDE4OkRpc2N1c3Npb25DYXRlZ29yeTMyNTMyMjc0', 'repository_id': 9052236, 'emoji': ':pray:', 'name': 'Q&A', 'description': 'Ask the community for help', 'created_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'updated_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'slug': 'q-a', 'is_answerable': True}, 'answer_html_url': 'https://github.com/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1954#discussioncomment-435903', 'answer_chosen_at': '2021-03-06T13:56:11.000Z', 'answer_chosen_by': {'login': 'pditommaso', 'id': 816968, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjgxNjk2OA==', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/816968?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/pditommaso', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/pditommaso/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'user_view_type': 'public', 'site_admin': False}, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1954', 'id': 3250668, 'node_id': 'MDEwOkRpc2N1c3Npb24zMjUwNjY4', 'number': 1954, 'title': 'is nextflow mixing up channel data when run in parallel?', 'user': {'login': 'DanielAmsel', 'id': 28996902, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjI4OTk2OTAy', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28996902?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/DanielAmsel', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DanielAmsel/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'user_view_type': 'public', 'site_admin': False}, 'labels': [], 'state': 'open', 'state_reason': None, 'locked': False, 'comments': 3, 'created_at': '2021-03-05T14:29:33Z', 'updated_at': '2022-07-18T08:08:14Z', 'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': '## Bug report \r\n\r\nHi, \r\nI wrote a nextflow script that takes input data and does something with the data in several dockerized processes.\r\nIn a final step, I want to merge the results of different processes into one process that creates a final output.\r\nNextflow runs in parallel for several data samples, each with a different ID.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior and actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe final merged results should come from data with the same ID, since it was the only input for the individual nextflow run.\r\n\r\nActually it seems that nextflow mixes up data from other runs that are performed in parallel.\r\nIn the work directory, I also find folders with different IDs in it.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nInput data ID-1 --> processing --> result comes from ID1 and ID2\r\nInput data ID-2 --> processing --> result comes from ID2 and ID1\r\nInput data ID-3 --> processing --> result comes from ID3\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce the problem\r\n\r\nJust run the script again, but the IDs that are mixed up change each time. \r\n\r\n\r\n### Environment \r\n\r\n* Nextflow version: [19.10.0.5169 and 20.10.0.54.31] \r\n* Java version: [openjdk 11.0.10]\r\n* Operating system: [Ubuntu]\r\n* Bash version: (GNU bash version 4.4.20(1))\r\n', 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1954/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1954/timeline'}, {'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow', 'category': {'id': 32532274, 'node_id': 'MDE4OkRpc2N1c3Npb25DYXRlZ29yeTMyNTMyMjc0', 'repository_id': 9052236, 'emoji': ':pray:', 'name': 'Q&A', 'description': 'Ask the community for help', 'created_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'updated_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'slug': 'q-a', 'is_answerable': True}, 'answer_html_url': None, 'answer_chosen_at': None, 'answer_chosen_by': None, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1959', 'id': 3255418, 'node_id': 'MDEwOkRpc2N1c3Npb24zMjU1NDE4', 'number': 1959, 'title': "Seeing Aborted Processe with errorStrategy = 'finish'", 'user': {'login': 'bgobbi', 'id': 17731370, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjE3NzMxMzcw', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17731370?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/bgobbi', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bgobbi/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'user_view_type': 'public', 'site_admin': False}, 'labels': [], 'state': 'open', 'state_reason': None, 'locked': False, 'comments': 2, 'created_at': '2021-03-09T00:39:24Z', 'updated_at': '2022-07-20T13:20:08Z', 'author_association': 'NONE', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': "I am seeing that after an error of one task other parallel executed tasks running on slurm are aborted even though I specified `errorStrategy = 'finish'` for the given process.\r\nIs this expected?\r\n\r\nAlso a related question. I would like my errorStrategy to be that all tasks that do not depend on the failed task are executed and run to completion. I have raid the [documentation](https://www.nextflow.io/docs/latest/process.html#errorstrategy) and none of the implemented strategies seems to do exactly that.\r\nIs there a way?\r\n\r\nThanks!", 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1959/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'timeline_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1959/timeline'}, {'repository_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nextflow-io/nextflow', 'category': {'id': 32532274, 'node_id': 'MDE4OkRpc2N1c3Npb25DYXRlZ29yeTMyNTMyMjc0', 'repository_id': 9052236, 'emoji': ':pray:', 'name': 'Q&A', 'description': 'Ask the community for help', 'created_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'updated_at': '2021-01-31T15:04:22.000Z', 'slug': 'q-a', 'is_answerable': True}, 'answer_html_url': None, 'answer_chosen_at': None, 'answer_chosen_by': None, 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nextflow-io/nextflow/discussions/1960', 'id': 3255637, 'node_id': 'MDEwOkRpc2N1c3Npb24zMjU1NjM3', 'number': 1960, 'title': 'the modules field in the weblog message for a started event in a DSL2 workflow', 'user': {'login': 'zhangzhen', 'id': 782824, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjc4MjgyNA==', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/782824?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/zhangzhen', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/zhangzhen/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/user